01
Services
Nuru Massage

An erotic massage technique in which one or more masseuses rub their body against the clients’ body after both parties are nude and covered with odorless and tasteless massage oil.

Deep Tissue

It involves applying sustained pressure using slow, deep strokes to target the inner layers of your muscles and connective tissues.

Swedish Massage

Circular pressure applied by the hands and palms, firm kneading, light tapping, and more. By using lighter, more general strokes such as effleurage and petrissage.

Cupping Therapy

Soft silicone cups are placed over tight areas of the body, gently suctioning the tense tissues up into the cups, and creating a bit of space between the bottom of the muscle and the top of the bones.

Hot Stone Massage

During a hot stone massage, smooth, flat, heated stones are placed on specific parts of your body. The stones are usually made of basalt, a type of volcanic rock that retains heat.

Sports Massage

It works by stretching tight muscles, stimulating inactive muscles, and improving the condition of the soft tissue. It will also help you exercise more efficiently and prevent some of the common ailments that go with exercise.

COVID-19 Safety Protocols

Relax.
We're COVID-19
ready.

Taking care of yourself shouldn’t be stressful. From traffic, to crowds at brick and mortar locations, Soothe removes these stressors from the equation. Just clear a space. Providers on the Lust Touch adhere to your local public health requirements as well as our own safety protocols. Relax knowing everything is handled. 05
Your safety is

Our Priority

Your safety comes first

We know that you won’t be able to relax and enjoy your massage unless you feel 100% comfortable with your therapist. And your therapist needs to know that they will be safe when meeting new clients at their home or office. So we place the highest priority on safety.

For client safety, our therapists undergo:

  • Multiple in-person interviews
  • Police background check
  • Reference checks
  • Practical exam

For therapist safety, our clients must:

  • Book Online
  • Validate appointment
  • Provide the booking confirmation code
